The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a labeled tree from independent traces, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithms provided for reconstructing the labels of certain classes of trees involve combinatorial and complex analytic methods, which are also relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the problem of string trace reconstruction, which is a special case of tree trace reconstruction, is a well-studied problem in machine learning (cs.LG).
